      "description": "This FD-generation RX-7 retains its iconic 13B-REW rotary engine, featuring the complex sequential twin-turbocharger system that provides a seamless torque curve. The drivetrain is paired with a precise five-speed manual gearbox and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. Recent preventative maintenance includes a full vacuum line refresh and an upgraded aluminum radiator to manage thermal loads effectively. The lightweight chassis utilizes a sophisticated four-wheel double-wishbone suspension, offering tactile feedback and neutral handling characteristics. While the paint displays minor road wear, the mechanical vitals are robust, with strong compression and a clean turbo spool. A well-sorted example of 90s JDM engineering.",
